# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version if you intend
#   for other developers to use the same version of Python.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if used with a database, you may need:
#   Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock is database-dependent and may not be shared.
#   poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock may not be shared.
#   pdm.lock

# PEP 582; used by e.g. github.com/pdm-project/pdm
